<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-29T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-29T10:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.21/205.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-29T10:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1913—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department received note from the Minister of Colombia dated November 24
                            requesting that reply to Legation’s October 22, 7 p.m., be
                            expedited.</p>
                        <pb facs="0432" n="328" xml:id="pg_328"/>
                        <p>Please inform Minister for Foreign Affairs that enormous pressure of
                            other vitally important matters has prevented the President from
                            receiving this question. It is hoped reply may be sent next week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>